guad0400.13:
{
}As sole protectors of the {MCR:s0Dl26:"Farplane"},{
}the {MCR:s06l4F:"Guado"} are the supreme race of {MCR:s0Dl03:"Spira"}.{PAUSE}{
}We are fundamentally different from the{
}populous humans and the hulking {MCR:s06l51:"Ronso"}.{PAUSE}{
}But, that’s an old story. Now the {MCR:s06l4F:"Guado"}{
}seek harmony with other races.

guad0400.15:
{
}Lord {MCR:s06l27:"Jyscal"}, back from the {MCR:s0Dl26:"Farplane"}?{
}Hahaha, you must be joking!{PAUSE}{
}He passed away in peace,{
}leaving the leadership to Lord {MCR:s06l33:"Seymour"}.{PAUSE}{
}He would never come back to haunt us.

guad0400.17:
{
}Perhaps Lord {MCR:s06l27:"Jyscal"} wanted to{
}see his son’s new bride.{PAUSE}{
}Even maesters of {MCR:s06l3F:"Yevon"} dote on{
}their children sometimes.

guad0400.18:
{
}Speaking of the incident now{
}will only cloud the joy of the wedding.{
}Say nothing.

guad0400.19:
{
}Following a half-human was our{
}fatal mistake.{PAUSE}{
}{MCR:s06l33:"Seymour"} destroyed the {MCR:s06l4F:"Guado"} single-handedly.{
}Him alone.

guad0400.20:
{
}{MCR:s06l10:"Tromell"} now spends his days mourning{
}on the {MCR:s0Dl26:"Farplane"}. You won’t get{
}a word out of him.

guad0400.21:
{
}You find it difficult telling{
}us {MCR:s06l4F:"Guado"} apart, don’t you?{PAUSE}{
}I suppose you think we{
}all look the same.

guad0400.23:
{
}My mother passed away{
}a long time ago.{PAUSE}{
}But I can always visit the{
}{MCR:s0Dl26:"Farplane"} whenever I need her.

guad0400.31:
{
}We’re always practicing{
}out in the {MCR:s0Dl24:"Moonflow"}.{PAUSE}{
}But the other day a shoopuf passed{
}by and nearly flattened us!

guad0400.33:
{
}It’s true that many tossed themselves to{
}the {MCR:s0Dl26:"Farplane"} in Lord {MCR:s06l33:"Seymour"}’s name.{PAUSE}{
}But until recently, I looked up to{
}him so much.{PAUSE}{
}So I suppose I’d be a{
}hypocrite to belittle him.

guad0400.35:
{
}Say, you play for the {MCR:s06l42:"Besaid Aurochs"}.{
}You’re {PC:00:TIDUS}, right?{PAUSE}{
}I saw you at the tournament.{
}Let’s blitz sometime.

guad0400.37:
{
}Aren’t you headed to {MCR:s0Dl29:"Macalania"}?{
}Better not keep them waiting.{PAUSE}{
}Lord {MCR:s06l33:"Seymour"} may be cool,{
}but {MCR:s06l10:"Tromell"} has quite a temper, you know.

guad0400.39:
{
}Our captain is aiming for{
}bigger goals now.{PAUSE}{
}He says he’ll take the helm of the {MCR:s06l4F:"Guado"}!{
}I wonder if he’s really serious.

